</font></big><p align="center"><font color="#0E024D" face="Arial"><big><strong>NECROMANCER FAQ</strong></big></font></p>
<div align="center"><center>

<table border="0" cellpadding="5" cellspacing="0" width="80%">
  <tr>
    <td width="100%" height="18" bgcolor="#0E024D"><font color="#FFFFFF" face="Arial"><strong><small>Why
    won't my pet respond to my commands?</small></strong></font></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width="100%" height="18"><small><font face="Arial">Your pet will not respond to your
    commands once it is out of range.&nbsp; They can get out of range very quickly, so it is a
    good move to make hotkeys for the generic commands such as back off, follow me, and kill.</font></small></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width="100%" height="18" bgcolor="#0E024D"><font color="#FFFFFF" face="Arial"><strong><small>When
    can my pet dual wield?</small></strong></font></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width="100%" height="18"><font face="Arial"><small>Your pets can dual wield from the
    level 29 pet and onwards.&nbsp; Not all the Level 29 summoning's will produce a pet
    capable of dual wielding but all pets from 34 onwards can without a problem.&nbsp; The
    level 34 summoning has a much better chance of producing a level 29 + pet than the level
    29 summoning, but it is not guaranteed.</small></font></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width="100%" height="18" bgcolor="#0E024D"><font color="#FFFFFF" face="Arial"><strong><small>How
    do I make my pet wield a weapon?</small></strong></font></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width="100%" height="18"><small><font face="Arial">To make your pet wield a weapon
    simply give the weapon to them.&nbsp; Note that you will not get the weapon back once
    given to the pet.&nbsp; It is gone for good.&nbsp; So don't give your latest pet a demon
    claw ok?</font></small></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width="100%" height="18" bgcolor="#0E024D"><font color="#FFFFFF" face="Arial"><strong><small>Does
    it matter what weapon I give him?</small></strong></font></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width="100%" height="18"><small><font face="Arial">Yes.&nbsp; However it works
    differently to normal players.&nbsp; With pets the only thing which a weapon will impact
    is the speed of attack.&nbsp; Generally the best weapons to use are the 19 speed Fine
    Steel Daggers, or 20 speed store bought daggers.&nbsp; Good alternates are short swords,
    rapiers and scimitars.&nbsp; Two handed weapons should be avoided.</font></small></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width="100%" height="18" bgcolor="#0E024D"><font color="#FFFFFF" face="Arial"><strong><small>Where's
    my Level 29 Pet spell?</small></strong></font></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width="100%" height="18"><small><font face="Arial">You can find you level 29 pet
    within an Elven City.&nbsp; Rumors also have it to exist somewhere in the Ocean of Tears.</font></small></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width="100%" height="18" bgcolor="#0E024D"><font color="#FFFFFF" face="Arial"><strong><small>Why
    do guards keep attacking me?</small></strong></font></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width="100%" height="18"><small><font face="Arial">Unfortunately as a necromancer
    everyone pretty much hates you.&nbsp; After all you spend all day bringing back to life
    the creatures they spend all day killing.&nbsp; Guards in most towns will attack you on
    sight until you have increased your faction with them by killing their enemies.</font></small></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width="100%" height="18" bgcolor="#0E024D"><font color="#FFFFFF" face="Arial"><strong><small>Is
    there anywhere I am not Kill On Sight?</small></strong></font></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width="100%" height="18"><font face="Arial"><small>When you start off you will have
    sufficient faction to be safe within the walls of your home city.&nbsp; As time goes on
    your faction in your home town, and other towns, will change.&nbsp; Eventually you can be
    safe within a few towns, but don't ever expect to be warmly welcomed into everyone home.</small></font></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width="100%" height="18" bgcolor="#0E024D"><font color="#FFFFFF" face="Arial"><strong><small>Are
    my lifetaps unresistable?</small></strong></font></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width="100%" height="18"><font face="Arial"><small>Once upon a time this was the
    case.&nbsp; However, as of November 1999, patches were implemented instituting the normal
    6 level limit on these spells.&nbsp; Even so many Necromancers have found the resists even
    on yellows and light reds to be quite high, and you should try and get an Enchanter,
    Shaman or Magician to debuff the enemy to increase the chance of your spell success.</small></font></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width="100%" height="18" bgcolor="#0E024D"><font color="#FFFFFF" face="Arial"><strong><small>What
    should I specialise in?</small></strong></font></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width="100%" height="18"><font face="Arial"><small>Both Alteration and Conjuration are
    very good choices.&nbsp; Alteration effects your lifetap series, whilst conjuration
    effects more of the powerful Damage over Time spells the necromancers get.&nbsp; Check the
    spell list to see what spells are available.</small></font></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width="100%" height="18" bgcolor="#0E024D"><font color="#FFFFFF" face="Arial"><strong><small>Can
    I have a pet and charm an undead as well?</small></strong></font></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width="100%" height="18"><small><font face="Arial">No.&nbsp; You can only ever be in
    command of one pet-type creature at once.&nbsp; If you have a pet you cannot charm an
    undead.&nbsp; Like wise if you have charmed an undead you cannot summon a pet.</font></small></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width="100%" height="18" bgcolor="#0E024D"><font color="#FFFFFF" face="Arial"><strong><small>What
    kind of armor can I wear?</small></strong></font></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width="100%" height="18"><font face="Arial"><small>You can wear any armor which is
    cloth based.&nbsp; This also includes robes.&nbsp;</small></font></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width="100%" height="18" bgcolor="#0E024D"><font color="#FFFFFF" face="Arial"><strong><small>Can
    I heal my pet?</small></strong></font></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width="100%" height="18"><small><font face="Arial">Yes you can both heal and buff your
    pet.&nbsp; Mend Bones, and Renew Bones can help keep your pet fighting longer.</font></small></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width="100%" height="18" bgcolor="#0E024D"><font color="#FFFFFF" face="Arial"><strong><small>Where
    do I get my research book?</small></strong></font></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width="100%" height="18"><small><font face="Arial">Your research book can be bought
    from your guild and is called the Book of Dark Bindings.</font></small></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width="100%" height="18" bgcolor="#0E024D"><font color="#FFFFFF" face="Arial"><strong><small>Where
    do I get research words?</small></strong></font></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width="100%" height="18"><small><font face="Arial">Research words can be found on the
    corpses of the enemies you slay.&nbsp; You can also buy them off players who have found
    them as loot.&nbsp; Most words are found through trading.</font></small></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width="100%" height="18" bgcolor="#0E024D"><font color="#FFFFFF" face="Arial"><strong><small>What
    languages do I need for research?</small></strong></font></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width="100%" height="18"><font face="Arial"><small>Elder Elven and Old Erudian are the
    languages of the research recipe books you can purchase from the necromancer guild. &nbsp;
    They are not actually required for the combining of words however.</small></font></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width="100%" height="18" bgcolor="#0E024D"><font color="#FFFFFF" face="Arial"><strong><small>I
    have been looking everywhere, but I can't find some of my spells!</small></strong></font></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width="100%" height="18"><font face="Arial"><small>Shadow Knights share many spells
    with necromancers.&nbsp; Some of your spells can only be found in their guilds, such as a
    number of the mid-level pet spells.&nbsp; Some other spells can be found in other caster
    guilds, such as the shielding line.</small></font></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width="100%" height="18" bgcolor="#0E024D"><strong><font color="#FFFFFF" face="Arial"><small>Should
    I spend practice points to increase my casting skills?&nbsp; (i.e.: alteration,
    conjuration, etc)</small></font></strong></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width="100%" height="18"><small><font face="Arial">No!&nbsp; You will be using these
    skills so often they will fly up!&nbsp; Save these skills for Meditation at level 4 (1
    point) and Research and Specialisation at later levels.&nbsp;</font></small></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width="100%" height="18" bgcolor="#0E024D"><strong><font color="#FFFFFF" face="Arial"><small>Where
    is my Class Specific Armor Found?</small></font></strong></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width="100%" height="18"><font face="Arial"><small>Necromancer armor is found off
    Boogeymen in the Plane of Fear.&nbsp; It is known as Blighted Armor.</small></font></td>
  </tr>
